parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric power steering assist can cause the steering wheel to become difficult or impossible to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult or impossible to turn
the power steering assist warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle loses power steering assist
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver
the power steering assist fails intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: jerking or stuttering of the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle and Acceleration Control Sensor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the throttle and acceleration control sensors can cause loss of acceleration, jerking or stuttering of the vehicle, and difficulty shifting gears.
symptoms: jerking or stuttering of the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Accelerator pedal seizure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injury or death, as the occupants of the vehicle are not protected from the impact.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in the event of a crash
despite the severity of the impact warranting deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall has left many vehicles with defective airbags that can cause serious injury or death in the event of a crash. The lack of available replacement parts has delayed the repair process, leaving vehicles on the road with potentially deadly airbags.
symptoms: dealerships claiming lack of parts or uncertainty about recall status due to Takata bankruptcy.
